sources.description: The Dark Past is a 1948 American psychological thriller FILM NOlR directed by Rudolph Maté, and starring William Holden, Nina Foch, and Lee J. Cobb. The film is a remake of Blind Alley (1939), and based on a play by American playwright James Warwick.   You can find out more about this movie from Wikipedia .
